OL,3,C'Worrying' drop in university
OL,4,Capplications from 18-year-olds in Wales
OL,6,FThe proportion of 18-year-olds in
OL,7,FWales applying to go to university has
OL,8,Fdropped to a 15-year low, with the gap
OL,9,Fbetween Wales and the rest of the UK
OL,10,Fnow at its widest, new figures show.
OL,12,FThe number of applicants from Wales is
OL,13,F20,960, which is lower than any point
OL,14,Fsince 2008, when there were 20,580
OL,15,Fapplicants.
OL,17,FHigher education experts have
OL,18,Fsuggested the drop could have long
OL,19,Fterm implications for Wales.
